UPDATE `posts` SET `id` = 44,`user_id` = 3,`title` = 'How to set up Sublime Text, Github, Filezilla, Remote Webhost over SFTP (SSH) with a Laravel 4 Web Application.',`slug` = 'how-to-set-up-sublime-text-github-filezilla-remote-webhost-over-sftp-ssh-with-a-laravel-4-web-application',`content` = 'I have an existing project under development.  I am switching workstations.  I want to move my project from Computer A to Computer B. This took several hours for me&nbsp;to figure out, but here it&nbsp;is so it can hopefully now be done in just a few minutes:\r\n<span><br>\r\n</span>\r\n<br><span><br>\r\n</span>\r\n<h2><b>How\r\nto establish a SFTP connection to your hosting account with\r\nFileZilla:</b></h2>\r\n<br><a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://kb.siteground.com/how_to_establish_sftp_connection_to_hosting_with_filezilla/">http://kb.siteground.com/how_to_establish_sftp_connection_to_hosting_with_filezilla/</a><span><br>\r\n</span>\r\n<span><br>\r\n</span>\r\n\r\n<br><span><br>foobar!<br></span><br>',`meta_title` = 'The Power of SFTP',`meta_description` = 'I have an existing project under development.  I am switching workstations.  I want to move my project from Computer A to Computer B.  Here it is in just a few minutes:',`meta_keywords` = 'How to, set up, Sublime Text, Github, Filezilla, Remote Webhost, SFTP, SSH, Laravel 4, Web Application',`created_at` = '2013-06-17 09:20:06',`updated_at` = '2013-06-18 10:54:13',`image` = 'screen/sublime.png' WHERE `posts`.`id` = 44;
UPDATE `posts` SET `id` = 45,`user_id` = 3,`title` = 'The best reason to develop on Linux: ',`slug` = 'the-best-reason-to-develop-on-linux',`content` = 'The remote server also runs on linux... this is very handy when it comes to understanding things like directory permissions and syntax when interacting with things like git. &nbsp;Perhaps the mac world is similar, but windows is not the right environment to learn in.<br><br>Linux is faster. &nbsp;It loads faster, it shuts down faster, it&nbsp;<br><br>Updates and Backups are automatic and elegant. &nbsp;It''s down to nearly one-click functionality. &nbsp;The user&nbsp;<br><br>doesn''t freeze very often, and it''s reliance on the CLI interface is efficient and helpful. &nbsp;<br><br>The CLI is great. &nbsp;When the development process&nbsp;comes to other situations which require the CLI, it''s nice to have been recently using it for other tasks.<br><br>Linux is more secure. &nbsp;It is unlikely you are going to attempt to download malicious software on linux. &nbsp;I nearly said, "it is less likely you are going to download malicious software", but the more correct answer is: "you are unlikely to download malicious software". &nbsp;<br><br>I am a fan of Microsoft Office products. &nbsp;I am not a fan of their marketing tactics or the prices they charge in comparison to the excellent software available in the Open Source world. &nbsp;It is not comparable in&nbsp;',`meta_title` = '',`meta_description` = '',`meta_keywords` = '',`created_at` = '2013-06-18 11:06:30',`updated_at` = '2013-06-18 11:06:30',`image` = 'screen/linux.png' WHERE `posts`.`id` = 45;
UPDATE `posts` SET `id` = 46,`user_id` = 3,`title` = 'Wordpress vs. Laravel',`slug` = 'wordpress-vs-laravel',`content` = 'Sorry if I ramble a bit. &nbsp;I have experimented with this a great deal, and over the past few months, I have built sandbox demo sites in all of the following:<br>Wordpress.comWordpress.orgLaravel 3Laravel 4 BetaLaravel 4 stable<br>I would enjoy discussing any aspect of these in detail, please let me know if you''re interested and I can provide links.<br>---<br>Laravel is more than a theme builder.<br>If I may extract a few phrases from the original query:<br>You asked:&nbsp;<br>"I want to know if I can make wordpress plugins and themes using Laravel, or whether I should be doing things another way."<br>I thought you said:<br>"should i be going things the other way around"<br>rephrase:&nbsp;&nbsp; -can i make wordpress plugins in laravel&nbsp; -can i make laravel plugins in wordpress&nbsp; -can i make wordpress themes in laravel&nbsp; -can i make laravel themes in wordpress<br>Let''s now discuss plugins vs. themes:<br>Themes, in my opinion, are VIEWISH. &nbsp;At least they should be. &nbsp;I use themes to create front-end styles, and some core structure like navigation, pages vs. posts, etc. &nbsp;It''s all very BLOGGISH in wordpress if you ask me. &nbsp; Wordpress also has nice admin interface, site stats, etc.<br>What is wordpress?&nbsp;What is laravel?&nbsp;<br>Performance?<br><br>let''s continue:<br>Wordpress vs. Laravel<br>Laravel itself being modular, and itself being a "laravel plugin", we should compare each available Wordpress with each available Laravel plugin:<br>Now that we''ve compared the individual plugins, let''s consider the methods of adding them. &nbsp;Site maintenance, extend-ability, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp; -What''s it take to develop a plugin in wordpress? &nbsp;&nbsp; -What''s it take to develop a plugin in Laravel?<br>PS: I read a good article the other day about how it is a big deal how Laravel has managed to decouple so many things... How does decoupling apply to wordpress?<br>What is the wordpress equivelent of laravel''s features:&nbsp; -PHP 5.37?&nbsp; -Artisan CLI?&nbsp; -Eloquent ORM?&nbsp; -Migrations?<br>Are any of these tools important to you when building your application? &nbsp;Will we use this work again?<br>Community: wordpress vs. laravel? (short and long-term)Installation: wordpress vs. laravel? (short term)<br>rephrase:wordpress vs. symfonywordpress vs. Eloquentwordpress vs. composerwordpress vs. packagistwordpress vs. TDDwordpress vs. Jeffrey Way<br><br><br>&nbsp; &nbsp; return View::make(''you''(''Winner/Laravel'') <br>Wordpress MVC Laravel MVC<br><a target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://laravel.com/</a>" title="Laravel Features" target="_blank"&gt;<a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://laravel.com/">http://laravel.com/</a><br>Wordpress is my preferred blog tool, except for the bugs...&nbsp;<br><br><br>Why re-write any code that you don''t have to? &nbsp;Use the program, or one of it''s available plugins. &nbsp;Make your own plugin. &nbsp;Make your own theme. &nbsp;Re-use it.<br>Wordpress Theme is comparable to Bootstrap, Symfony, Blade... Use Wordpress if all you need is quick &amp; dirty pages, posts, stats, etc. and you are most comfortable with it. &nbsp;But ask yourself this: what will it take to re-use your work? &nbsp;How will you implement it? &nbsp;Did you say copy and paste?<br>Laravel is the better all around tool to build modular flexible web applications. &nbsp;If you are used to wordpress, and you need a quick &amp; dirty, rusty old tool to fulfill your website''s needs, then use wordpress.<br>Some keywords:&nbsp;<br>If you''re most familiar with it, use wordpress.Not planning on maintaining it? &nbsp;Wordpress.Not building any further functionality?Not interested in &nbsp; Simple blog : use wordpress.<br>Laravel is tightly wound with bootstrap.<br>Plugins and themes...<br>Are you after display? &nbsp;Plugins are quite different from themes, or at least they should be. &nbsp;To me, themes are style-related. &nbsp;Plugins are&nbsp;<br>I also feel a lack of control at a certain point. &nbsp;Wordpress is a user interface for blogging, site statistics, and themes, but falls short in "back-end".<br>Laravel requires php 5.3. &nbsp;Wordpress requires php 4.0.<br>Rephrasing this point: the foundation of the Wordpress is php 4 point whateverthe foundation of Laravel is php 5.3.7. &nbsp;&nbsp;<br>If you have to choose one for all around development purposes... like "which one would I rather use?" &nbsp;there is no quesiton. &nbsp;If you are familiar with the Wordpress tools, use them. &nbsp;<br>tags:<br>Here are some links:<br><a target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://forums.laravel.io/viewtopic.php?id=5359</a>" target="_blank"&gt;<a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://forums.laravel.io/viewtopic.php?id=5359">http://forums.laravel.io/viewtopic.php?id=5359</a><br><a target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17062182/what-problems-could-i-meet-with-laravel-4-on-php-5-3-3/1...</a>" target="_blank"&gt;<a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17062182/what-problems-could-i-meet-with-laravel-4-on-php-5-3-3/17078845?noredirect=1#comment24745816_17078845">http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17062182/what-problems-could-i-meet-with-laravel-4-on-php-5-3-3/1...</a><br>Connecting the two is very interesting. &nbsp;Why reinvent the wheels that wordpress has solved? &nbsp;Same the other way around. &nbsp;<br>Wordpress Plugins for Bootstrap?<br>Jyle, it''s been 4 months: how did this work out for you? &nbsp;Looking back, how would you answer your own question today?<br>I will now attempt to build wordpress plugin for laravel. &nbsp;If you look for it, you will find it. &nbsp;If you build it, they will come.<br>you said:&nbsp;<br><br>Input and Advice appreciated<br><a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17062182/what-problems-could-i-meet-with-laravel-4-on-php-5-3-3/17078845?noredirect=1#comment24745816_17078845">http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17062182/what-problems-could-i-meet-with-laravel-4-on-php-5-3-3/1...</a><br>I say:Thank you and all for the same!<br><br><br><a target="_blank" rel="nofollow" href="http://wordpress.org/about/">http://wordpress.org/about/</a><br>',`meta_title` = 'Wordpress vs. Laravel',`meta_description` = 'aka Laravel vs. Wordpress - aka what''s&nbsp;Extensible php development all about?',`meta_keywords` = 'wordpress, laravel, php, development',`created_at` = '2013-06-19 13:12:46',`updated_at` = '2013-06-19 14:23:49',`image` = 'screen/wordpress.png' WHERE `posts`.`id` = 46;
